The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bangaloreplays Trump card

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Ivanka Trump: All smiles

 Bangalore, April 26: Donald and Ivanka Trump, children of showman billionaire Donald J. Trump, landed in Bangalore today in search of investment opportunities. 

 The Trump kids, both vice-presidents of the Trump Organisation, called on Karnataka chief minister H.D. Kumaraswamy to discuss the investment climate and opportunities in Karnataka.

 We welcome all investors and we will also provide all necessary co-operation, the chief minister said.

 Government sources said the Trump siblings were briefed on the states plan to develop infrastructure in tier II cities of Belguam, Hassan, Mangalore, Mysore and Gulburga to create jobs. 

 I am impressed with the Bangalore city and its tremendous growth potential. It is amazing the way it has grown over the last decade. I had read and heard a lot about Bangalore and this is my first visit and I am already in love with it, Ivanka said reacting to the chief ministers query about her impression.

 We are here to explore the investment potential of the state and for understanding its requirement, Trump junior said.




